<item>
            <title>[LU-13412] fix read if readahead window smaller than rpc size</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13412</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt; Readahead always try to align readahead with RPC size, but this&lt;br/&gt;
 could introduce a problem if readahead window is smaller than RPC size.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; With current codes, it will fallback a lot of 4k read because most of readahead stop, fix this to align with readahead window rather than RPC size in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
